# Spring Boot slice testing (external cherry-pick)

Source: [jabrena/cursor-rules-java](https://github.com/jabrena/cursor-rules-java) rule 311 — adapted for your monorepo.

## Prefer slice tests over full context

| Layer | Annotation | Use when |
|-------|------------|----------|
| Web layer | `@WebMvcTest(controllers = X.class)` | HTTP contract, status codes, JSON shape |
| JPA slice | `@DataJpaTest` | Repository queries (if JPA present) |
| JSON | `@JsonTest` | Serializer/deserializer edge cases |

## Rules

- Mock only **direct** collaborators with `@MockitoBean` (Spring Boot 3.4+) or `@MockBean`.
- Do **not** load full `@SpringBootTest` for controller-only changes.
- Use `@Import` for security/`GlobalExceptionHandler` when needed.
- Assert HTTP + JSON body; avoid asserting internal service call order unless behavior-critical.

## Conflicts

If this file conflicts with [`java-springboot-standards.mdc`](../java-springboot-standards.mdc) or ArchUnit tests, **Agentic Loop standards win**.
